We recommended that the:

Human Resource Management Officer (a) submit justification on the necessity of hiring of 198 job-order personnel and 33 contract of service for CY 2019; (b) conduct a thorough study and evaluation of the Municipality’s needs for additional personnel to avoid excessive hiring of individuals under contract of services and/or job orders and the duplication of the work being undertaken by regular employees, and provide this Office a copy of such study; (c) as a control measure, ensure that all the job order contracts entered into by the Municipality clearly indicate the specific work or task to be assigned to each job order to facilitate comparison with the actual and accomplishment report; and (d) ensure that all DTR system-generated and accomplishment report will be signed by the job-order and contract of service personnel and certified by their respective supervisor;

Municipal Accountant record in the appropriate expense account the payment of wages of the job-order personnel under the Office of the Municipal Health Officer, Hospital Administrator-Designate of RUR Hospital, Municipal Mayor, Municipal Mayor under LEEPU Manager, Tourism Officer Designate, BPLO, HRMO-Designate,  Waterworks Supervisor-Designate, MENRO, Municipal Treasurer, Acting Municipal Accountant, Municipal Agriculturist, MPDO, Municipal Engineer, and General Services Officer in accordance with the provision of COA Circular 2015-009 dated December 1, 2015.

