We recommended that the Municipal ICO-Treasurer: 

ensure that collections of the collectors are within the maximum cash accountability allowed in their fidelity bond, if possible, coordinate with the Bureau of Treasury for the increase in their fidelity bonds;

refrain from issuing accountable forms to non-bonded employees pursuant to Bureau of Treasury, Treasury Circular No. 02-2009 dated August 5, 2009. Likewise, ensure that non-bonded employees are properly supervise by the bonded employee and install control measures in the collection of the non-bonded employees; 

discontinue the practice of keeping large amount of collections in their hand/possession to avoid possible loss and misappropriation. Likewise, deposit the collections intact every day or as frequently as possible;

require the Liquidating Officer to verify whether the collections pertaining the used and all issued accountable forms are remitted before new series of receipts will be issued to collectors; and 

submit comments/justification on the above noted observation in the collection and deposit, and issuance and use of accountable forms.

We recommended that the:

BAC Chairperson submit written explanation/justification on (i) Bid Securing Declaration was accepted even it is not included in the list of acceptable bidding security; (ii) recommending award of Orconuma-Mina de Oro to Alberto Uy Construction and Development even validity of the posted bid security already lapsed; (iii) recommending issuance of Notice of Award even without actual cash available; and (iv) recommending award of Orconuma-Mina De Oro FMR to Alberto Uy Construction and Development even performance security was not posted;

Management submit written explanation/justification on entering into a contract agreement for Rehabilitation of ANILORCU Communal Irrigation System even beyond the 10-days prescribed period from the receipt of NOA; 

Municipal Engineer submit written explanation/justification on (i) preparing opening and graveling of Anilao FMR even minimum requirements set by DPWH is a concrete pavement as per DO 11 s. 2014; (ii) completion of the projects beyond the original contract expiry that resulted to incurrence of liquidated damages of King’s Builders and Development Corporation for the Construction of Sagana Health Building; and (iii) defects noted in the technical inspection of the project that resulted to total cost deficiency of ₱860,386.03;

OIC-Municipal Accountant (i) submit written explanation/justification on non-imposition of warranty security to the Anilao FMR and Orconuma – Mina De Oro FMR; and (ii) demand for refund from (1) King’s Builders and Development Corp the liquidated damages incurred for the delayed implementation of Sagana Health Building amounting to ₱162,371.69, and cost deficiency totalling ₱228,849.78 due to defects noted by the COA TAS in the Anilao FMR and ANILORCU Irrigation System; and (2) Alberto Uy Construction and Development cost deficiency totalling ₱631,536.25 due to the defects noted by the COA-TAS in the pavement of Orconuma – Mina De Oro FMR, to avoid disallowance in audit; and

OIC-Municipal Accountant and BAC Chairperson submit all the lacking documents to avoid suspension in audit.

We recommended that:  
(a) The Implementing Office submit the documents needed to validate the compliance of the Municipality with the provisions of DILG MC No. 2014-96 dated August 12, 2014 to avoid suspension in audit;  
(b) The Municipal Engineer compute the days the contractor is in delay and require the contractor to pay for liquidated damages; 
(c) The BAC Chairperson, Municipal Engineer, Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer explain the above noted observations regarding the procurement and implementation of the projects; and 
(d) The Municipal Accountant, BAC Chairperson and Municipal Engineer submit all the lacking documents to avoid suspension in audit.

We recommended that: 
(a) GAD Focal Person and HRMO provide explanation on the charging of team-building related expenses to Gender and Development Fund of the Municipality; 
(b) Management provide guidelines in the conduct of the team-building activities;
(c) The Municipal Accountant submit all supporting documents pertaining to the TEV claim, to avoid suspension in audit; and 
(d) The Municipal Accountant provide explanation on the difference cited for the payment of transportation. Likewise, strictly follow the guidelines for excessive, extravagant and unnecessary expenses cited in COA Circular 2012-003 and properly plan each activity so they can have savings for important projects/activities beneficial to most constituents of the Municipality.

